Master Brand Identity

The following pages articulate the proper use of the ANC visual brand assets. We must follow these guidelines rigorously to protect the foundational elements upon which our brand is built. Adhering to these guidelines will allow us to communicate our brand in a consistent, compelling and unified manner. Correct application is crucial in helping our brand maintain and communicate our unique position throughout the competitive landscape of event technology solution providers.

Logo Misuse Examples

Illustrated here are several examples of ANC logo misuse. Please refrain from presenting the logos in any ways that violate the guidelines set forth in this deck. The logo should NEVER be stretched or squished. Logo should NEVER incorporate a drop shadow. NEVER rotate any element within the logo. The logo should NEVER be skewed. Backgrounds should NEVER be so bold or so high in contrast that the logo loses impact. Logo should NEVER incorporate an outline. The colors of the logo should NEVER be altered. The logo should NEVER be altered in any way. X X 5555 X

Clear Space

The new ANC logo has been hand-crafted. As such, the spatial relationships between the characters should never be altered. Additionally, the ANC logo requires clear space around it so as to not allow graphics or other visual elements to compromise its legibility and/or visual integrity.

Brand Architecture System

Below are a few URL Logo choices to use when applying the company url to advertising, signage, proposals, etc. Please do not alter in any way.

ANC LiveSync Logos

Owned and operated by ANC, LiveSync is an event technology software product that may or may not be used by clients in conjunction with ANC installations. Therefore, they may or may not include the Powered by ANC strap line. Note the use of the secondary palette blue for the Sync part of the name.

LOOK TOOLS KIT

PART 02

Graphics & Photographic Treatment

The slash pattern has been developed for use on most or all ANC branded applications the website, background art, cover / divider pages for decks & proposals, merchandise, social platforms, etc. As demonstrated here, the slash pattern is a sharp, angled graphic treatment composed of a series of blues from the primary and secondary color palettes. It can be applied to dark, light or white backgrounds with solid or outline / linear slashes. The angle of the slashes should never deviate away from 55. The slash pattern is most effective when used in conjunction with approved photography that has been altered to reflect the ANC color palette.
